# The repository is checked out with core.autocrlf=true on Windows, which would
# otherwise rewrite these files to CRLF and break them:
#
#   *.sh   a CRLF shebang makes Linux fail with "bad interpreter: ^M"
#   *.tsv  the manifest is read field-by-field by fetch-dataset.sh; a trailing
#          \r rides along on the last column and corrupts the byte-size
#          arithmetic
#
# Pinning eol=lf keeps both correct on every platform. PowerShell is content
# with LF, so fetch-dataset.ps1 needs no exception.
*.sh text eol=lf
*.tsv text eol=lf
